WEBVTT

00:02.044 --> 00:03.580
NARRATOR:
Previously on Sons of Anarchy:

00:03.754 --> 00:05.745
CLAY:
A donation for the Cacuzza charity fund.

00:05.923 --> 00:09.086
And a case of Glocks for your trouble.

00:09.259 --> 00:11.250
Yeah, that works.

00:14.848 --> 00:16.304
Okay.

00:17.685 --> 00:19.095
What are you doing with Lowen?

00:19.269 --> 00:22.227
You divorcing Jax? You're planning on
some kind of custody coup?

00:22.398 --> 00:25.014
What I do is none of your business.
Bitch.

00:25.192 --> 00:26.648
Aah!
GEMMA: Jesus.

00:26.819 --> 00:29.435
UNSER: What the hell?
My baby. Look what you did.

00:29.613 --> 00:30.898
I didn't do that.

00:31.073 --> 00:32.529
Yes, you did. We all saw it.

00:32.700 --> 00:35.362
I don't ever want her near our children again.

00:37.287 --> 00:39.414
Promise me.
JAX: I promise.

00:39.581 --> 00:42.243
You will never see those kids again.

00:42.418 --> 00:45.910
Grandma is dead.

00:46.088 --> 00:49.171
You know it's not you
who deserves to be in jail.

00:49.341 --> 00:51.548
Full immunity for the proof
of the gunrunning.

00:52.094 --> 00:53.800
It's the only offer you'll get.

00:54.972 --> 00:57.384
I don't need to think about an offer.

00:57.558 --> 00:59.173
JAX:
I'm here to make you an offer.

00:59.351 --> 01:03.936
Galen O'Shay.
I will deliver him with a shipment of guns.

01:04.106 --> 01:05.391
Open and shut.

01:05.566 --> 01:07.272
What's in it for you?
JAX: Immunity.

01:07.443 --> 01:10.310
For the MC, for all gun charges,
past and present.

01:10.487 --> 01:13.695
And I figure you also have
a personal request.

01:14.199 --> 01:16.406
You need to look at Tara's case again.

01:17.327 --> 01:19.989
You should go back,
take another look at what happened.

01:20.164 --> 01:22.951
Find the truth in all this.
You think my wife is a liar?

01:23.125 --> 01:24.831
[BOTH GRUNTING]

01:25.294 --> 01:27.706
Break it up.
Stop it! Jackson!

01:27.880 --> 01:32.374
Honey, it was all a lie.
The pregnancy, the miscarriage.

01:32.551 --> 01:35.918
Tara wants out, Jax, from you, the club.

01:36.096 --> 01:39.509
This is the truth, and if she won't tell you...

01:39.933 --> 01:42.094
...you need to find someone who will.

01:42.269 --> 01:44.260
ls Tara divorcing me?

01:45.022 --> 01:47.889
Yes.
And taking my sons?

01:50.402 --> 01:51.778
JAX:
Get out!

01:53.906 --> 01:56.898
LOWEN [OVER PHONE]:
Tara, it's Ally Lowen.

02:05.125 --> 02:07.116
[CAR APPROACHING]

02:14.092 --> 02:15.548
[DOOR CLOSES]

02:18.388 --> 02:19.969
TARA:
No.

02:21.892 --> 02:23.678
Thomas?

02:25.312 --> 02:26.552
Oh, God.

02:27.523 --> 02:29.388
Abel?

02:36.615 --> 02:38.947
JAX:
You should let him sleep.

02:58.637 --> 03:00.548
Hi, sweetie.

03:02.558 --> 03:04.765
There'll be someone watching you.

03:04.935 --> 03:06.846
Don't try to take them anywhere.

03:08.605 --> 03:09.720
What are you gonna do?

03:10.983 --> 03:12.814
I don't know.

03:13.277 --> 03:15.734
I can't see anything right now.

03:15.904 --> 03:19.362
If I don't put some distance here,
someone's gonna get hurt.

03:26.748 --> 03:30.161
[KATEY SAGAL & THE FOREST RANGERS'
"FOR A DANCER" PLAYING]

03:32.087 --> 03:35.329
Keep a ﬁre burning in your eye

03:36.884 --> 03:40.172
Pay attention to the open sky

03:41.388 --> 03:47.554
You never know what will be coming down

03:50.981 --> 03:55.600
I don ’t remember losing track of you

03:55.777 --> 04:00.111
You were always dancing in and out of view

04:00.574 --> 04:06.695
I must have thought you'd always be around

04:06.872 --> 04:08.863
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

04:10.542 --> 04:16.208
Always keeping things real
By playing the clown

04:16.798 --> 04:20.757
Now you're nowhere to be found

04:29.436 --> 04:33.975
Don 't know what happens when people die

04:34.149 --> 04:37.767
Can't seem to grasp it as hard as I try

04:37.945 --> 04:42.530
It's like a song I can hear
Playing right in my ear

04:42.699 --> 04:45.315
That I can't sing

04:45.494 --> 04:48.406
Can't help listening

04:48.580 --> 04:53.199
Can't help feeling stupid standing round

04:53.377 --> 04:57.871
Crying as they ease you down

04:58.590 --> 05:04.301
'Cause I know that you’d rather
We were dancing

05:05.097 --> 05:09.466
Dancing our sorrows away

05:11.144 --> 05:14.136
Right on dancin'

05:27.327 --> 05:31.991
Keep a ﬁre for the human race

05:32.165 --> 05:36.499
Let your prayers go drifting into space

05:36.670 --> 05:42.506
You never know what will be coming down

05:46.513 --> 05:51.007
Perhaps a better world is drawing near

05:51.184 --> 05:55.348
And just as easy it could all disappear

05:56.023 --> 06:01.814
Along with whatever meaning
You might have found

06:05.699 --> 06:11.911
Don't let the uncertainty turn you around

06:12.080 --> 06:16.164
Go on and make a joyful sound

06:16.835 --> 06:21.454
Into a dancer you have grown

06:21.631 --> 06:26.751
From a seed somebody else has thrown

06:29.723 --> 06:34.717
Go on ahead
And throw some seeds of your own

06:34.895 --> 06:39.514
And somewhere between the time you arrive

06:39.691 --> 06:42.273
And the time you go

06:42.444 --> 06:46.938
May lie a reason you were alive

06:47.115 --> 06:50.733
But you’ll never know

06:55.540 --> 06:57.531
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

07:12.724 --> 07:14.965
Your lawyer say why?

07:15.602 --> 07:19.811
CLAY: Guess the judge wants to get out ahead
of all the bad press been falling on my club.

07:19.981 --> 07:24.099
Ain't easy pulling a jury that ain't been
exposed to all that shit, man.

07:24.277 --> 07:25.892
CLAY:
Yeah, I know.

07:26.071 --> 07:27.777
No.

07:39.251 --> 07:41.412
What the hell happened?

07:41.628 --> 07:44.165
Shrink double-dipped.

07:44.422 --> 07:46.834
Gave me to the guard I went off on.

07:48.718 --> 07:51.505
How'd you land back in gen pop?

07:52.681 --> 07:55.172
They yanked me out
to have a chat with my lawyer.

07:55.350 --> 07:57.011
My trial's been moved up.

07:58.562 --> 08:02.225
Yeah. They cart me off to county tomorrow.

08:02.566 --> 08:05.148
Shit. That's a problem.

08:06.903 --> 08:08.894
Yes, it is.

08:09.656 --> 08:12.944
You tell Galen.
You have him reach out to Jax.

08:13.827 --> 08:16.489
You able to make those business calls?

08:16.663 --> 08:19.200
Yeah, it's all in play.

08:19.958 --> 08:23.667
I had my lawyer get my old lady down here.
I'll take care of my personal shit...

08:23.837 --> 08:28.126
...but you tell Galen he has got
to make this happen tomorrow.

08:29.092 --> 08:30.457
All right?

08:30.886 --> 08:33.002
Pope was capital.

08:33.180 --> 08:35.762
That guilty verdict can send me anywhere.

08:35.932 --> 08:38.639
And then all this goes away.

08:40.604 --> 08:42.936
I'll pass it along.

08:50.530 --> 08:52.771
[CURTIS STIGERS & THE FOREST
RANGERS' "THIS LIFE" PLAYING]

08:52.949 --> 08:57.693
Riding through this world
All alone

08:57.871 --> 09:03.616
God takes your soul
You're on your own

09:04.127 --> 09:08.541
The crow flies straight
A perfect line

09:10.383 --> 09:14.797
On the devil's path
Until you die

09:17.307 --> 09:21.892
Gotta look this life
In the eye

09:31.112 --> 09:33.023
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

09:33.907 --> 09:35.067
Yes?

09:35.242 --> 09:37.073
MARGARET:
It's Margaret.

09:40.747 --> 09:42.408
Hi.

09:42.999 --> 09:46.412
I saw the boys were in day care.
I was hoping you might be here.

09:46.586 --> 09:48.247
Yeah.

09:48.505 --> 09:50.871
Just looking at...

09:51.258 --> 09:53.499
...Iawyer résumés.

09:53.677 --> 09:56.510
Why? What happened?

09:58.890 --> 10:00.391
Jax knows the truth.

10:01.935 --> 10:04.017
He threatened Lowen, and she...

10:05.146 --> 10:07.683
...told him everything.

10:10.902 --> 10:12.938
What did he do?

10:13.113 --> 10:15.445
TARA:
Well, he didn't hurt her.

10:15.699 --> 10:17.030
Me either.

10:17.200 --> 10:19.942
And I don't know
what pushed him at Lowen.

10:20.120 --> 10:21.951
Gemma.

10:22.122 --> 10:24.408
She came here yesterday.

10:24.791 --> 10:27.453
Said she knew
I forged documents to help you.

10:27.627 --> 10:30.004
Threatened to tell the hospital.

10:31.172 --> 10:35.962
She was bluffing,
but my response was too cavalier. |--

10:36.136 --> 10:37.626
She knew I was protecting you.

10:38.346 --> 10:40.132
What happened?

10:40.307 --> 10:42.138
I told her she couldn't prove anything.

10:42.309 --> 10:45.642
She said she didn't have to,
that her son would.

10:45.854 --> 10:48.812
She just needed a more reliable source
than a junkie.

10:49.649 --> 10:51.856
Wendy must have talked.

10:55.363 --> 10:57.820
I was afraid to go home last night, Tara.

10:59.159 --> 11:03.493
I told Dave
that I had to work through the night...

11:03.705 --> 11:05.866
...and I stayed here...

11:06.333 --> 11:08.073
...where I knew there were guards.

11:08.877 --> 11:13.712
No. No, Jax got his information from Lowen.
I really doubt he'd bother you.

11:13.882 --> 11:16.168
I can't take that chance.

11:16.760 --> 11:17.795
I'm sorry.

11:21.681 --> 11:23.012
Um....

11:23.183 --> 11:28.348
I've got three weeks of vacation and comp time,
and I'm gonna take them.

11:29.105 --> 11:31.517
I'm gonna stay with my sister in Sedona.

11:40.408 --> 11:42.524
I understand.

11:45.997 --> 11:47.862
I'm sorry.

11:51.378 --> 11:53.289
Thank you.

11:57.300 --> 11:59.507
Please be careful.

12:17.404 --> 12:18.940
WOMAN:
Thank you.

12:21.032 --> 12:22.738
Hey.

12:23.868 --> 12:25.984
Wasn't sure if you'd make it.

12:26.162 --> 12:27.948
I'm here.

12:30.125 --> 12:31.911
Showed up this morning.

12:32.085 --> 12:36.124
Diosa Del Sur Escorts and Massage,
officially in business.

12:36.297 --> 12:39.255
Ah, that's great.
COLETTE: Yes, it is.

12:39.426 --> 12:41.337
Thank you, gentlemen.

12:45.598 --> 12:48.635
I'm not sure what happened,
but no more fighting.

12:52.439 --> 12:55.272
I'll have Lyla come sit down with the girls.

12:55.442 --> 12:57.933
Get their info,
make sure we have everyone's W-93.

12:58.361 --> 13:01.774
Weed out anyone who's not up
to Diosa's very high standards.

13:01.948 --> 13:03.108
Something like that.

13:03.992 --> 13:06.529
You want me to put this someplace, sweetie?

13:06.703 --> 13:09.866
No. I got it, darling. Thank you.

13:11.082 --> 13:14.074
I'm just gonna crash here for a few nights,
if you don't mind.

13:15.003 --> 13:17.494
Of course not. Come on.

13:19.674 --> 13:21.289
Put your stuff in my room for now.

13:22.302 --> 13:23.633
JAX:
I appreciate that.

13:24.012 --> 13:26.594
Any reason
why you're not sleeping at home?

13:26.764 --> 13:29.016
Ah, you don't wanna know.

13:29.225 --> 13:31.716
You're probably right.

13:33.980 --> 13:36.972
Hey.
Hey.

13:37.525 --> 13:38.810
What's going on?

13:38.985 --> 13:41.397
I got a Clay thing.

13:41.988 --> 13:43.353
We've got an Irish thing.

13:44.824 --> 13:46.815
Use my office.

13:47.660 --> 13:49.491
Thanks.

13:53.708 --> 13:54.743
Gemma Teller.

13:55.376 --> 13:57.367
Colette Jane. Pleasure.

13:58.505 --> 14:00.666
That's what I hear.

14:09.140 --> 14:10.425
Clay wants to see me.

14:11.684 --> 14:14.426
Lawyer says he can get me in
this afternoon.

14:14.771 --> 14:16.853
Did he say why?

14:17.065 --> 14:19.681
Papers he wants signed, something like that.

14:20.360 --> 14:22.851
It's probably just an excuse for a sit-down.

14:25.573 --> 14:27.074
What's going on with the Irish?

14:30.537 --> 14:32.573
It's okay. He knows most of it.

14:34.666 --> 14:37.032
Okay. Galen's in town.

14:37.210 --> 14:40.953
Says we have to see him,
Nor-U-Bev, in 20 minutes.

14:41.172 --> 14:42.958
Got any idea what it might be?

14:44.926 --> 14:46.382
No.
HAPPY: We should get going.

14:46.761 --> 14:48.877
The bridge is gonna be jammed.

14:50.223 --> 14:52.805
I got something I need to tell you and Nero.

14:53.601 --> 14:56.388
TIG: You want us to split?
JAX: No.

14:57.438 --> 14:59.269
I want you to hear this too.

15:04.737 --> 15:07.729
I talked to Lowen last night.

15:09.951 --> 15:12.738
I got some truth
about what happened with Tara.

15:16.749 --> 15:19.240
She was never pregnant.

15:22.630 --> 15:25.246
Tara set up my mom.

15:25.800 --> 15:28.917
Made it look like a miscarriage...

15:29.262 --> 15:35.132
...so that I would sign off on Gemma never
becoming legal guardian of our sons.

15:38.771 --> 15:41.433
She wants to divorce me.

15:45.236 --> 15:47.727
She wants full custody,
and she was gonna split.

15:48.990 --> 15:50.651
BOBBY:
Jesus.

15:52.619 --> 15:53.734
What about jail?

15:54.746 --> 16:00.366
Well, if she served time, she was gonna
make sure Wendy became the guardian...

16:00.543 --> 16:03.785
...and that she got my sons out of Charming.

16:11.304 --> 16:12.840
I'm sorry I didn't believe you.

16:15.183 --> 16:17.299
How could you?

16:18.311 --> 16:19.517
I'm so sorry, honey.

16:23.149 --> 16:26.641
JAX: I'm sorry, man.
I know, mano. It's okay.

16:30.490 --> 16:32.776
What do you wanna do, brother?

16:34.077 --> 16:37.490
I got West watching Tara right now.

16:37.789 --> 16:39.654
Making sure she doesn't go anywhere.

16:41.834 --> 16:43.995
None of this makes sense to me right now.

16:44.170 --> 16:47.333
Ijust think I need a couple days,
figure it out.

16:47.507 --> 16:49.998
She doesn't know West.

16:50.218 --> 16:53.005
Might be better
if she had a familiar face behind her.

16:54.722 --> 16:58.055
Keep her motivated to stay close to home.

16:58.226 --> 16:59.341
I can watch her.

17:01.854 --> 17:04.516
Yeah? Thanks.

17:04.691 --> 17:07.728
We're here, man.
Let us know if you need anything.

17:11.114 --> 17:14.026
All right, let's just get out of here.

17:14.784 --> 17:16.365
You handle this?

17:16.536 --> 17:18.026
Yeah, I got it.

17:22.375 --> 17:23.455
I'm sorry.

17:26.337 --> 17:29.921
You be careful with Clay.
I'll be fine.

17:30.091 --> 17:32.628
Be careful with the Butcher of Belfast.

17:33.886 --> 17:36.468
I'll try to stay in one piece.

17:37.890 --> 17:40.597
I'll see you later.
JAX: Yeah, you will.

17:47.734 --> 17:51.727
How Iong's he been dipping into that?
Not long.

17:52.280 --> 17:54.145
He's working out his mommy issues.

17:54.323 --> 17:55.733
[CHUCKLES]

17:56.617 --> 17:58.608
How about you, pimp daddy?

17:59.120 --> 18:00.860
You wanna work out some mommy issues?

18:01.038 --> 18:02.619
Hey, that's why I'm with you, Mommy.

18:02.790 --> 18:04.246
[GEMMA CHUCKLES]

18:04.417 --> 18:06.578
Let me spank that brown ass.

18:09.589 --> 18:10.999
Be careful.

18:20.266 --> 18:22.097
GALEN:
Consider it handled.

18:22.268 --> 18:24.304
We'll talk when it's done.

18:24.479 --> 18:28.188
They're here now.
CONNOR: Jackson. Thanks for coming...

18:28.357 --> 18:30.939
...on such short notice.
JAX: Yeah.

18:31.110 --> 18:33.396
So, what's so important?

18:34.530 --> 18:36.691
It's all about the timing, son.

18:36.908 --> 18:38.990
Heard Clay made his calls?

18:39.535 --> 18:42.447
Yup. Everyone's locked down
except the Italians.

18:42.622 --> 18:44.783
Cacuzza's undecided.

18:46.959 --> 18:50.122
That's your biggest customer.
Three families, two territories.

18:50.296 --> 18:51.797
I know.

18:51.964 --> 18:53.955
He's weighing an offer from the Chinese.

18:54.342 --> 18:57.800
I thought Jimmy was loyal to Clay.
JAX: He is.

18:57.970 --> 19:01.554
Just trying to make us do a little dance
for their business.

19:01.724 --> 19:04.306
So when do you talk?
HAPPY: We're on our way from here.

19:04.477 --> 19:08.220
Cacuzza's meeting with us first.
Then the Lin family.

19:09.690 --> 19:11.817
I figured we'd show him
some of the new mods.

19:11.984 --> 19:13.144
GALEN:
Already assembled.

19:13.694 --> 19:17.403
Got nine cases of the AKs
with the new scopes and grips.

19:17.573 --> 19:18.608
We can bring them to the meet...

19:18.783 --> 19:20.193
...help you close the deal.

19:20.368 --> 19:23.405
That's okay. I'll get Cacuzza on board.

19:23.579 --> 19:25.991
GALEN:
No doubt. Butjust take Connor.

19:26.499 --> 19:27.739
Shows respect.

19:27.959 --> 19:30.371
Lets them know
how much we value their business.

19:30.545 --> 19:32.331
It makes sense.

19:32.755 --> 19:33.835
I'll let you run it.

19:35.842 --> 19:39.505
No time for discussion, son.
We need to close the deal today.

19:40.012 --> 19:41.263
What's the big rush?

19:41.848 --> 19:44.339
Why I asked you here.

19:44.559 --> 19:47.346
Clay's trial has been moved up.

19:47.562 --> 19:49.473
They transport him tomorrow.

19:50.439 --> 19:51.724
[JAX SIGHS]

19:51.899 --> 19:53.514
Shit.
GALEN: Aye.

19:53.985 --> 19:57.068
Complicates our plan.
Gonna need some help.

19:57.280 --> 19:59.066
[SCOFFS]

19:59.240 --> 20:01.356
We're not part of taking down that transport.

20:01.534 --> 20:06.369
I have the vehicles, the route, the plan.
It'll happen without a hitch.

20:07.373 --> 20:11.366
I can't get a crew here in time.
Need about six of your men.

20:11.878 --> 20:14.210
And what if we say no?

20:20.887 --> 20:22.297
You really can't, Jackson.

20:23.890 --> 20:28.805
Take it to your table, have one of your votes,
but we both need this to happen.

20:29.020 --> 20:32.103
Moves guns fonNard for us,
puts them behind you.

20:38.613 --> 20:40.569
All right, I'll get you an answer.

20:41.073 --> 20:45.237
Have a few more details to lock down.
Then I can bring you all up to speed.

20:45.745 --> 20:48.282
Yeah, okay.

20:51.751 --> 20:53.537
So, what?

20:53.794 --> 20:56.251
What do we do about Clay?

20:57.131 --> 20:59.838
I don't think we have much of a choice.

21:00.051 --> 21:02.258
We don't have time to take it to the table.

21:02.428 --> 21:06.091
If we don't wanna do this,
we gotta find somebody who will.

21:06.265 --> 21:08.677
I'll call T-M, get the vote.

21:08.851 --> 21:13.015
Jax, Galen's a lunatic, but he's smart, man.

21:13.189 --> 21:16.773
No matter what the plan is,
they're not gonna put themselves at risk.

21:16.943 --> 21:18.934
I know. That's the problem.

21:19.111 --> 21:22.353
Irish will die before they get caught.
CHIBS: Aye.

21:23.157 --> 21:27.867
And if this shit goes sideways,
they're gonna blast a very bloody way out.

21:29.497 --> 21:31.988
We're so damn close.

21:33.209 --> 21:36.872
I don't want our last push out of guns
to end in a pile of dead cops.

21:37.838 --> 21:39.829
TIG:
It won't, brother.

21:40.675 --> 21:42.256
[JAX SIGHS]

21:49.517 --> 21:52.224
HAPPY:
Yeah. No, I know. I know.

21:53.604 --> 21:55.140
Uh-huh.

21:56.148 --> 21:58.059
All right. All right, late.

21:58.234 --> 22:01.818
Talked with everyone.
They're good with helping the Irish.

22:05.241 --> 22:06.822
Okay.

22:06.993 --> 22:09.200
Looks like we're in.

22:19.130 --> 22:21.667
Door's almost shut, brother.

23:07.887 --> 23:09.593
Yeah, yeah. Either one would be good.

23:10.222 --> 23:11.723
Nothing sooner?

23:11.891 --> 23:15.679
Okay. No, no, no, I can't. I can-- I did.

23:16.228 --> 23:19.265
Okay, okay, okay, thanks. Just forget it.

23:19.440 --> 23:20.646
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

23:20.816 --> 23:22.067
Shit.

23:31.827 --> 23:34.318
TARA:
I know you're in there, Wendy.

23:36.165 --> 23:37.826
[SIGHS]

23:40.836 --> 23:44.328
Hey. What's going on?

23:54.100 --> 23:58.139
I know you told Gemma everything.

24:00.606 --> 24:03.689
What do you think happens now? Hmm?

24:03.859 --> 24:05.770
To both of us.

24:06.278 --> 24:09.065
Can't be any worse
than anything that's already happened.

24:13.536 --> 24:14.571
Jesus Christ.

24:18.374 --> 24:20.285
Are you high?

24:20.876 --> 24:22.457
No.

24:23.087 --> 24:25.920
I'm just trying to get
on the other side of it now.

24:41.313 --> 24:43.144
Jax...

24:43.649 --> 24:45.514
...knows everything.

24:46.777 --> 24:48.392
Do you know what that means?

24:49.697 --> 24:52.814
He'll have the claim against Gemma
thrown out...

24:52.992 --> 24:55.529
...and she'll get custody of my boys
if I go tojail.

24:57.329 --> 24:59.615
I'm sorry.
No.

25:01.000 --> 25:02.160
What were you thinking?

25:03.210 --> 25:05.872
I wasn't.
What the hell does that mean?

25:06.046 --> 25:08.833
It means, Tara,
if I were capable of being a mother...

25:09.008 --> 25:12.000
...I never would've agreed to help you.

25:12.178 --> 25:13.634
Because it was wrong.

25:13.804 --> 25:16.341
Well, your Hazleton hindsight
doesn't help me right now.

25:16.974 --> 25:18.305
Thanks, I get it.

25:19.185 --> 25:20.846
Look, I don't wanna use again.

25:21.020 --> 25:26.435
I'm just trying to get myself into sober living
or rehab or anything.

25:31.864 --> 25:35.857
God, Tara, you gotta come clean.

25:36.035 --> 25:39.323
Just talk to Jax, talk to Gemma.
They already know the truth.

25:39.496 --> 25:43.034
They don't know your truth.
Tell them why you really did this.

25:43.209 --> 25:46.042
Let them see the pain that you've been in.
And then what?

25:46.212 --> 25:50.421
Beg them for forgiveness?
No. Just stop lying.

25:50.591 --> 25:51.831
It's the right thing.

25:54.511 --> 25:57.844
Everything I did was right.

25:58.015 --> 25:59.846
Tara, I'm sorry.

26:00.017 --> 26:02.178
Stop it. You are not sorry.

26:02.353 --> 26:06.221
Do you know why you're not capable
of being a mother? Because you're a coward.

26:09.276 --> 26:11.232
I'm not afraid of them.

26:11.403 --> 26:12.734
Not anymore.

26:12.905 --> 26:16.193
What is that supposed to mean?
It means you're a stupid, weak junkie.

26:27.836 --> 26:29.576
[ENGINE STARTS]

26:32.758 --> 26:34.919
[CAR ENGINE STARTS]

26:37.137 --> 26:38.923
Shit.

26:45.271 --> 26:47.512
Crazy bitch.

27:02.121 --> 27:04.112
Jimmy.

27:04.290 --> 27:07.157
How are you, man?
Ah, we're okay.

27:07.960 --> 27:11.248
Not too thrilled about having
to put on a gun-and-pony show.

27:11.422 --> 27:12.457
CACUZZA:
I know.

27:13.132 --> 27:16.340
But I got a lot of years
sitting around my table too, Jax.

27:16.552 --> 27:19.840
Aldo's known old man Lin
since before you were born.

27:20.055 --> 27:23.468
I gotta honor that,
talk to Henry and his uncle...

27:23.642 --> 27:26.179
...at least hear what they got to say.

27:29.148 --> 27:30.263
Idsh?

27:35.654 --> 27:40.648
Yeah. Yeah, they wanted to be here.
Show respect.

27:42.995 --> 27:44.951
Mr. Cacuzza.

27:45.122 --> 27:47.329
Galen O'Shay, Connor Malone.

27:47.499 --> 27:50.081
Pleasure.
CACUZZA: Gentlemen.

27:51.003 --> 27:54.666
Made quite a commute for this sales call.
We think your business is worth it.

27:54.840 --> 27:56.205
CACUZZA:
Wow.

27:56.383 --> 28:01.002
I should do this more often.
You guys are great for my esteem.

28:01.180 --> 28:02.636
What do we got?

28:02.806 --> 28:07.550
Handguns you know.
Glocks are full auto with the extended clips.

28:07.728 --> 28:12.472
AKs are original Russian stock.
Fully updated, new action, quick load.

28:12.649 --> 28:14.685
Military handles?
GALEN: Aye.

28:14.860 --> 28:16.851
Absorb 50 percent more recoil.

28:17.029 --> 28:18.985
It's the new Elcan scope.

28:26.038 --> 28:28.370
BOBBY:
Yo, Jax. Chinese.

28:38.008 --> 28:39.509
Try the scope.

28:39.676 --> 28:42.338
Can split a Protestant hair
from three blocks away.

28:42.513 --> 28:45.255
Ah, good Catholic boy.

28:49.228 --> 28:51.560
Yeah. That feels good.

28:51.730 --> 28:53.186
They work even better on flesh.

28:55.442 --> 28:58.354
Put it down! Down!
Chibs, don't.

28:58.529 --> 28:59.894
Go! Go! Go!

29:00.072 --> 29:01.403
[SPEAKS IN CHINESE]

29:07.246 --> 29:09.077
What the hell was that?

29:09.915 --> 29:13.282
That was just me letting you know
how much we want your business, Jimmy.

29:16.547 --> 29:19.755
Apologies for the blood,
but a strong message was needed.

29:19.925 --> 29:22.462
I'm sure you can understand
the importance of that.

29:22.886 --> 29:24.092
Mm.

29:24.263 --> 29:25.719
What message was that?

29:26.223 --> 29:29.386
We're the only source for guns
in Northern California.

29:29.560 --> 29:30.595
Lin knew that.

29:30.769 --> 29:35.138
That kind of undermines the free-market
strategy that we were attempting here.

29:35.315 --> 29:38.102
GALEN:
We have better guns, better price.

29:38.277 --> 29:40.438
Did you know this was going down?

29:41.196 --> 29:44.063
No, this wasn't the way
I planned to get your business, Jimmy.

29:44.616 --> 29:48.074
GALEN: You've been paying
20 percent above cost. I'll drop it to 10...

29:48.245 --> 29:50.657
...for the next year
while Clay makes the transition.

29:50.831 --> 29:54.323
After that it tops out at 18 percent.

29:54.501 --> 29:57.243
This is gonna upset some of my people.

29:58.422 --> 30:02.916
Ten percent for 18 months.
Then itjumps to 15.

30:09.308 --> 30:12.516
Two years at 10 percent. Then itjumps to 12.

30:16.815 --> 30:18.351
Fair enough.

30:19.109 --> 30:21.020
Do we have a deal?
CACUZZA: Yeah.

30:21.236 --> 30:23.978
I think I can make everyone understand.

30:25.824 --> 30:27.485
Excellent.

30:27.659 --> 30:30.526
Throw the body in the car.
CONNOR: Go get it.

30:31.538 --> 30:33.995
Did you discuss the new arrangements
with your table?

30:34.166 --> 30:36.498
Yeah, we're good with that.

30:37.294 --> 30:39.330
But this shit?

30:39.880 --> 30:42.997
This is a complication.
GALEN: No, it's not.

30:43.759 --> 30:47.251
Gentlemen. Been a pleasure.

30:48.388 --> 30:50.470
I didn't know this was coming.

30:50.974 --> 30:52.555
Sorry.

30:58.023 --> 31:00.309
Your partner knows how to close a sale.

31:00.484 --> 31:02.770
JAX:
Yeah. I'm sorry.

31:02.945 --> 31:04.685
Now you know why we're getting out.

31:07.074 --> 31:09.030
Don't sweat it, kid.

31:09.409 --> 31:11.786
I was never gonna go with the Chinks.

31:17.042 --> 31:20.705
Try to get ahold of Lin or the old man.
We need to clean this shit up.

31:20.879 --> 31:22.540
CHIBS:
Trust me, I'm on it.

31:25.551 --> 31:28.258
There's no way Lin's gonna believe
we didn't plan this.

31:28.428 --> 31:31.511
We burn the Chinese,
things are gonna jump off in Oakland.

31:32.349 --> 31:33.714
Then what happens?

31:35.936 --> 31:38.552
Then we lose the balance.

31:58.584 --> 32:00.825
UNSER:
I just got a call from Wendy.

32:01.003 --> 32:04.166
Tara went to her place.
Very pissed off.

32:04.339 --> 32:07.251
Said she seemed unraveled.
What does that mean?

32:07.426 --> 32:11.419
I don't know, but we just sent Rat
to pick up Juice and his bike.

32:11.597 --> 32:13.553
Tara backed over him to lose the tail.

32:13.724 --> 32:15.009
Damn.

32:15.183 --> 32:17.390
Where are the boys?
They're still at day care.

32:17.561 --> 32:19.426
GEMMA: ls Juice okay?
Yeah. He'sjust pissed.

32:20.105 --> 32:22.721
All right, tell Rat to take Juice down
to St. Thomas.

32:22.899 --> 32:24.730
Keep an eye on those boys.
UNSER: Yeah.

32:24.901 --> 32:27.438
I think I'd better be the one
to go look for Tara.

32:27.613 --> 32:31.856
I think you should check on Wendy.
She didn't sound so good.

32:32.034 --> 32:34.116
High?
Uh, sick.

32:36.204 --> 32:39.196
No, you gotta go check on Wendy.
I gotta go see Clay.

32:39.583 --> 32:42.450
What do you do about Tara?
Let her unravel.

32:42.628 --> 32:46.746
Maybe I should go with you, talk to Wendy.

32:46.923 --> 32:48.538
Junkie to junkie.

32:48.717 --> 32:51.208
Yeah, if you want.
I'll drive.

32:51.386 --> 32:52.421
In that?

32:52.888 --> 32:55.755
Come on, Wayne,
it'll get you in touch with your inner cholo.

32:55.932 --> 32:59.265
I had that removed with my spleen.

33:00.729 --> 33:04.062
That's a little cancer humor.
Right.

33:04.483 --> 33:06.394
UNSER:
I'll call Rat.

33:08.904 --> 33:10.986
GEMMA:
Just a heads-up:

33:11.156 --> 33:14.489
He's kind of in love with me. Have fun.

33:58.495 --> 34:00.486
[LOCK CLICKING]

34:10.465 --> 34:11.875
I didn't know anyone was here.

34:15.971 --> 34:17.927
What do you want?

34:18.682 --> 34:21.719
Coming by to get
some of the boys' things.

34:22.144 --> 34:24.851
Just in case they need
to spend some time at Grandma's.

34:25.522 --> 34:28.389
Yeah, that's not gonna happen.
Really?

34:31.486 --> 34:35.855
And what is it you think
is going to happen, Tara?

34:40.370 --> 34:43.828
You know why you hate
what I did so much?

34:45.167 --> 34:47.704
Because it's something
you would've done.

34:49.045 --> 34:51.878
You've been my teacher, Gemma...

34:53.592 --> 34:56.425
...my old-lady coach
since I came back to Charming.

34:56.595 --> 34:58.756
Thought you would've been
proud of me...

34:58.930 --> 35:01.672
...pushing the envelope
to protect my family.

35:01.850 --> 35:05.388
Yeah, there's a lot of things I'd do
to protect my family.

35:05.687 --> 35:09.179
Faking the death of a baby,
that ain't one of them.

35:10.108 --> 35:12.440
Oh, guess I misjudged you.

35:12.611 --> 35:15.774
I didn't realize you had a line
that couldn't be crossed.

35:16.782 --> 35:19.945
Seems you misjudged everyone, darling.

35:20.410 --> 35:22.401
That's why you're all alone.

35:23.955 --> 35:25.866
Get out of my house.

35:28.293 --> 35:30.033
Or what?

35:31.546 --> 35:33.207
You gonna run me over?

35:35.133 --> 35:40.423
Your bridges are all burning. I'd think you'd be
trying to make as many friends as possible.

35:40.597 --> 35:43.760
I don't need friends. I have my family.

35:44.142 --> 35:46.303
You honestly believe that, don't you?

35:52.484 --> 35:55.021
How'd you think
this was gonna play out?

35:55.278 --> 35:58.065
Best-case scenario, your plan worked.

35:58.949 --> 36:00.610
You divorce Jax...

36:00.784 --> 36:07.121
...either you or Wendy take those boys
on up to Oregon or wherever.

36:08.667 --> 36:12.080
Did you really think
Jax was gonna let that happen?

36:12.254 --> 36:13.835
He'd have no choice.

36:15.257 --> 36:18.499
Do you have any idea who your husband is?

36:18.677 --> 36:21.339
What he's capable of?
I know him better than you do.

36:24.432 --> 36:26.172
Oh, no.

36:26.977 --> 36:28.842
Clearly you don't.

36:30.856 --> 36:33.063
My son loves deep...

36:33.859 --> 36:36.350
...hates deeper.

36:36.862 --> 36:39.103
It's in our genes.

36:40.699 --> 36:43.611
Betrayal is unforgivable.

36:44.202 --> 36:48.366
What you did,
what you were planning to do...

36:48.707 --> 36:50.447
...there's no coming back from that.

36:52.878 --> 36:59.545
All you can do now
is tell him you're sorry and go away.

37:00.552 --> 37:02.884
I'll never do that.

37:03.388 --> 37:05.549
Not without my sons.

37:08.059 --> 37:10.311
You need to hear this, Tara...

37:11.021 --> 37:14.809
...and understand it on every level.

37:15.692 --> 37:19.480
Thomas and Abel will not be raised by you.

37:21.406 --> 37:27.618
What you do now will determine
how we deliver that message.

37:29.915 --> 37:32.031
Mommy moved away...

37:33.251 --> 37:35.708
...or Mommy passed away.

37:38.924 --> 37:40.755
Your call.

37:48.934 --> 37:50.140
[DOOR CLOSES]

38:09.579 --> 38:15.290
Couldn't connect with Lin or the uncle.
Tried the restaurant, warehouse. Nothing.

38:16.378 --> 38:18.539
Okay. Well, I'm gonna make sure...

38:18.713 --> 38:23.582
...that tomorrow's job doesn't end up
in a 44-minute gunfight with 200 sheriffs.

38:26.972 --> 38:28.963
[DIALING]

38:30.976 --> 38:34.389
How do you think this one plays out,
brother?

38:34.604 --> 38:40.144
I don't know, man. It's hard to unplug when
everybody depends on you for the power.

38:40.610 --> 38:42.225
[PHONE RINGS]

38:42.404 --> 38:43.439
Yes?

38:43.613 --> 38:45.478
MAN [OVER PHONE]:
I have Jax Tel/er on the line.

38:45.657 --> 38:48.399
Put him through.
MAN: Line two.

38:49.744 --> 38:51.484
Mr. Teller, how can I help you?

38:52.247 --> 38:55.489
We got our license for Diosa Del Sur today.

38:55.667 --> 38:56.907
Thank you.

38:57.419 --> 39:00.377
You're welcome.
Now it's your turn to deliver.

39:00.547 --> 39:03.835
I'll give you Galen O'Shay
within the next 48 hours.

39:04.676 --> 39:06.667
Can you be a little more specific?

39:06.845 --> 39:10.758
I'll meet you tomorrow,
give you all the details.

39:11.725 --> 39:13.511
Can you prove your end?

39:13.685 --> 39:16.893
I’ve drafted an immunity deal
for you and the club.

39:17.564 --> 39:21.102
Had my team set up
a plea agreement for Tara.

39:21.276 --> 39:25.565
There's some fines, community service,
but no jail time.

39:25.739 --> 39:27.400
JAX:
Good.

39:28.408 --> 39:32.071
Galen will have a large, well-armed crew.

39:32.537 --> 39:34.744
You're gonna need manpower, and lots of it.

39:35.790 --> 39:39.203
I’ll tell you where
and when to send them tomorrow.

39:39.461 --> 39:40.871
[LINE CLICKS]

39:48.928 --> 39:50.919
Think She'll take the bait?

39:53.183 --> 39:54.889
Depends what it is.

39:55.727 --> 39:58.469
Okay, boys, where to?

40:00.815 --> 40:02.897
Colette's.

40:34.140 --> 40:39.100
So you known Gemma
since she was, like, a kid, huh?

40:39.270 --> 40:40.726
Yeah.

40:41.439 --> 40:44.272
She as crazy then as she is now? Heh.

40:44.442 --> 40:45.978
Iguess.

40:50.615 --> 40:54.278
Jax's ex, this Wendy,
she been clean for a while?

40:56.162 --> 40:57.948
Yeah.

40:59.749 --> 41:01.159
She grow up here in Charming?

41:03.545 --> 41:04.660
No.

41:09.134 --> 41:13.218
So I guess the cancer's eaten away that part
of your brain that can hold a conversation.

41:13.388 --> 41:17.677
No, it's eaten away at my patience
for people I don't give a shit about.

41:18.643 --> 41:20.053
[CHUCKLES]

41:21.271 --> 41:22.306
For the record...

41:22.480 --> 41:23.640
...someone talks to me that way...

41:23.815 --> 41:27.023
...I usually grab their ass out of the car
and throw them a beat-down.

41:27.735 --> 41:30.477
Guess I'm getting a pardon
on account of my sickness.

41:31.030 --> 41:33.817
Hey, look, I've been dead twice.

41:33.992 --> 41:35.823
I've been cut open three times.

41:35.994 --> 41:39.578
I've got a kid with spina bifida.
Probably won't make it till he's 15.

41:40.039 --> 41:43.031
So your cancer,
it don't mean shit to me, man.

41:45.044 --> 41:49.413
I'm trying to make an effort here
because I know how much Gemma loves you.

41:50.508 --> 41:52.590
Trust me, I know how hard it is to earn that.

41:59.851 --> 42:02.388
Thanks for making me feel like shit.

42:03.855 --> 42:06.016
No problem, homes.

42:32.800 --> 42:34.006
Left side!

42:36.054 --> 42:37.965
[GUNFIRE]

42:38.348 --> 42:39.554
Jump off!

42:39.724 --> 42:41.555
[MAN SPEAKING IN CHINESE]

42:51.152 --> 42:53.313
[TRUCK HORN HONKING]

42:58.034 --> 43:00.195
[CAR HORN HONKS]

43:00.370 --> 43:02.361
[GUNFIRE]

43:37.782 --> 43:38.988
JAX: Shit.
CHIBS: Jax.

43:39.492 --> 43:41.198
You okay?
HAPPY: Pick him up.

43:41.411 --> 43:44.153
I'm all right. I'm all right.
MAN: Out, out, out! Now!

43:44.914 --> 43:46.450
HAPPY: Behind you.
Shit.

43:46.624 --> 43:48.285
CHIBS:
Jackie.

43:50.420 --> 43:52.035
Put them down. Put them down.

43:52.213 --> 43:54.920
CHIBS: All right.
All right, man. All right.

43:55.591 --> 43:57.582
[SPEAKING IN CHINESE]

44:06.644 --> 44:10.637
We got no control over what Galen does.
Get off of him.

44:10.857 --> 44:15.476
Psycho just cut two of my guys into pieces
and blew up our goddamn clubhouse.

44:18.364 --> 44:21.822
We got the cartel business with Henry.

44:21.993 --> 44:25.156
Why would we okay the Irish
to take him out?

44:25.621 --> 44:27.577
Relax.

44:27.957 --> 44:31.791
If I wanted you dead,
I could've killed you six times already.

44:33.254 --> 44:34.755
Well, what the hell do you want?

44:35.840 --> 44:38.331
You're getting out of the guns.

44:38.634 --> 44:40.170
We should have that business.

44:41.012 --> 44:43.594
The cartel shipments have been
grinding to a halt.

44:44.098 --> 44:49.183
We need the street. This is our territory.
We own it. We deserve it.

44:50.521 --> 44:52.512
It's not that simple, Sir.

44:54.609 --> 44:57.772
Then let me dumb it down for you, son.

44:58.488 --> 45:03.699
The only way any of you walk away from here
is if you shut down the Irish pipeline...

45:03.868 --> 45:07.986
...and my family take control
over the guns in Northern Californ.

45:15.546 --> 45:17.798
I guess I don't really have a choice, do I?

45:17.965 --> 45:20.547
No, you don't.

45:20.718 --> 45:26.054
And you close the deal when you tell me where
I can find Mr. Galen O'Shay and their guns.

45:27.225 --> 45:31.138
I need to even the score
after what they did today.

45:37.068 --> 45:39.650
Galen's got a shipment coming in tomorrow.

45:40.905 --> 45:43.988
Drop is at a new location.

45:44.742 --> 45:47.233
I'll let you know when and where.

45:48.246 --> 45:50.237
Okay.

45:50.832 --> 45:55.872
But I'll entertain one of your men until then.
Keep everyone honest.

45:56.921 --> 45:58.877
I like the crazy-looking one.

45:59.424 --> 46:00.539
HAPPY:
Get your hands off me.

46:00.716 --> 46:03.173
I'm not letting you take one of my guys.
Then I keep you.

46:03.344 --> 46:05.084
That ain't happening.
TIG: No, you're not.

46:05.263 --> 46:06.844
I'm cool, boss.

46:07.098 --> 46:08.929
You guys split.

46:09.100 --> 46:10.840
I'll chill with old Wang Chung.

46:14.772 --> 46:16.387
Get your hands off me.

46:17.608 --> 46:18.984
Tomorrow.

46:19.986 --> 46:22.068
HAPPY:
Get off me.

46:33.082 --> 46:34.743
What are you doing here?

46:35.460 --> 46:37.951
I always come to a hospital
when someone runs me over.

46:39.297 --> 46:41.253
Tell Jax I don't need a watchdog.

46:46.095 --> 46:49.383
I'm just keeping an eye
on Abel and Thomas.

46:49.557 --> 46:52.720
To make sure they don't go anywhere
they're not supposed to.

46:52.894 --> 46:54.634
A request of their grandmother.

47:01.027 --> 47:03.313
TARA: Where is he?
I don't know.

47:03.529 --> 47:06.236
Just tell me where he is, asshole.

47:09.118 --> 47:12.485
Diosa. Stockton.

47:12.663 --> 47:15.279
Meeting with his partner, Colette.

47:16.083 --> 47:18.825
Here, let me get you the address.

47:24.300 --> 47:26.507
That's her car down there.

47:27.136 --> 47:30.128
Wendy. You in there? It's Wayne.

47:30.306 --> 47:32.012
That's smoke, man.

47:32.183 --> 47:33.673
[UNSER GRUNTS]

47:33.851 --> 47:35.842
[BOTH SNIFFING]

47:37.188 --> 47:40.601
Shit, it's coming from inside. Wendy!

47:40.775 --> 47:42.515
Step back, step back.

47:42.693 --> 47:44.684
Kick right there. Right there.
All right.

47:46.322 --> 47:47.778
[UNSER COUGHS]

47:47.949 --> 47:50.190
NERO: Hey.
UNSER: Oh, man.

47:50.368 --> 47:52.108
